Tom Kellichan (born c. 1954) was the original drummer of The Skids, from 1977 to 1979.
From Cowdenbeath, and a former van driver, he completed the line-up of The Skids after answering their ad for a drummer.
After touring with the band in 1979, promoting Scared to Dance, he departed, being replaced by Rusty Egan.
After The Skids, he played drums for Bill Nelson (of Be-Bop Deluxe), in the song "Decline And Fall", for the Quit Dreaming And Get On The Beam album (1981).
